CDDS DATABASES AND DATABASES

This form is used to specify the databases in which the CDDS is present,
the replication support for the CDDS at that database, and the number of
the Replicator Server that will transmit replications to that database.

To complete this screen, enter the appropriate values for the CDDS.  Use
the Tab key to move from one column to the next.  Use the Newrow key or
the arrow keys to move between lines.  To remove a database, use the
RowDelete operation.  To save the definition, select the Save operation.

The columns on the list are:

        COLUMN NAME             DESCRIPTION
        -----------             -----------
        DB No                   A database number where the CDDS is
                                located.

        Vnode/Database Name     The virtual node name and the database
                                name. This field is automatically filled
                                in when the database number is entered.

        Type                    The CDDS Target Type at this database.
                                Possible values are:

                                1  Full Peer
                                2  Protected Read-only
                                3  Unprotected Read-only

                                Select the Subtopics menuitem for more
                                information.

        Description             Description of the CDDS Target Type.
                                This field is automatically filled in
                                when you specify the Target Type.

        Server                  The Replicator Server number assigned to
                                propagate transactions to that database
                                within the CDDS.


The menu commands are as follows:

        MENU COMMAND    SYNOPSIS
        ------------    --------
        Save            Save the definition and return to the CDDS
                        Summary screen.

        RowDelete       Delete the currently highlighted row.

        ListChoices     Display a list of acceptable values for the
                        current column.

        Help            Access the Help facility.

        End             Return to the CDDS Summary screen.
